      <section eId="sec_4502">
        <num>4502</num>
        <heading>Spouse</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_4502__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Incompetency where issue adultery. A husband or\nwife is not competent to testify against the other in an action founded\nupon adultery, except to prove the marriage, disprove the adultery, or\ndisprove a defense after evidence has been introduced tending to prove\nsuch defense.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_4502__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Confidential communication privileged. A husband or wife shall not\nbe required, or, without consent of the other if living, allowed, to\ndisclose a confidential communication made by one to the other during\nmarriage.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
